üèÅ How to Run & Use in Postman
Start PostgreSQL and create database course_api_db.

Set .env with proper credentials and JWT_SECRET.

Run:

bash
Copy
Edit
npx nodemon server.js
Endpoints:

Register:
POST /auth/register
Body { "name", "email", "password" } ‚Üí returns token.

Login:
POST /auth/login ‚Üí get your JWT token.

For all protected routes, set header Authorization: Bearer <token>.

Example CRU(D):

Users:
GET /users
GET /users/:id
PUT /users/:id
DELETE /users/:id

Address:
POST /users/:id/address

Enroll in courses:
POST /users/:id/enroll body: { "courseIds": [1,2] }

Courses:
CRUD under /courses

Posts:
POST /posts, GET /posts, etc.

‚úÖ Summary of Associations
User ‚Üî Address: one‚Äëto‚Äëone

User ‚Üî Post: one‚Äëto‚Äëmany

User ‚Üî Course: many‚Äëto‚Äëmany via join table UserCourses

‚úÖ Final Notes
Validations enforced using express-validator.

Passwords hashed with bcrypt.

Authentication via JWT tokens.

Default courses seeded at startup.

Easily test all endpoints via Postman by passing your token in Authorization header.

